// Frontend of Website --> Structure , Styling , Basic Functionalities
// Structure of the Website - HTMl
// Styling of the Website - CSS
// Functionality of Website - JS
// Basic Structure of HTMl
<html>
    <head>
        <Title>
 "My Document"
        </Title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>"Hello World</h1>
        <p>"Paragraph here</p>
    </body>
</html>

// Class and Id tags are attributes which access the tags

// id - is an attribute which is uniquely identifies a HTML tags
// Example of Unique id attribute
<h1 id=""Top Heading">"Hello World"</h1>
//Two or more tags cant have the same id

// Class - like id, its also an attribute which identifies one or more than one HMTL tags
// Class name need not be unique
// Example of id attribute
<h1 class="Heading">"Hello World"</h1>
<h2 class="Heading">"Hello from Chennai"</h2>

// Through class we get access to multiple tags. Through id we can get access to only one HTML tag

// CSS - Cascading Style Sheets.
// CSS controls the layput of multiple web pages and saves lot of time
// Through CSS can set colors - Inline , Internal and External

// Internal HTML tag
// External HTML tag

// Margin - It gives gap between the tag and its surrounding

